narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about analyzing cathedrals, the common stories they portrayed, and the context in which they were developed. The course was extremely interesting and Professor Bloch was very knowledgeable.

The focus (readings in particular) were on the age and less on the Cathedrals. Lectures were the reverse. All-in-all, it gave me a heightened appreciation for gothic architecture, the 12-13th century, and French history that I didnt have before.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Learned a lot but the length of classes may actually hurt learning since it is hard to stay focused and engaged looking at a screen for 3 hours and 15 minutes

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Definitely! For anyone interested in learning about Cathedrals and European history, this is an absolutely essential course.
